(468, 1, '2019-07-04 10:32:18', '2019-07-04 03:32:18', '“Success is just the first step for the next attempt”\n\nAs a result of enormous effort of the Organizer and active participation of exhibitors, VIETNAM HARDWARE &amp; HAND TOOLS 2019 has achieved surprisingly impressive results. More than 283 enterprises from 18 different countries and territories exhibited on the scale of 5000m2, Belgium, China, Denmark, Germany, Hong Kong, Italy, India, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Russia, Singapore, Spain, Switzerland, Thailand, Taiwan, USA, Vietnam. In addition, there are a wide range of the world major brands joining the Exhibition such as: BOSCH, ONISHI, KNIPEX, WIHA, WEDO, UNIQUE STAR, SWISSTECH, PUMA, KUNJEK, ITO, SB CORPORATION, NANIWA, STAR-M, THE HIVE, OMBRA, KENDO TOOLS, etc., along with Vietnamese brands like LIDOVIT, ANH DUONG, NHAT THANG, DINH LUC, T.A.T, TAN AN PHAT, MINH KHANG, SDS, MRO, etc., were on display. This is a significant event supporting the key industries to develop sustainably, namely: construction, automobile, road, shipbuilding, aerospace, woodworking, retail etc.The organizer organized several commercial connection activities between sellers and buyers, including forum about Hardware and Hand Tools industry, Seminar: “ Enhancing Living Standards and Home Improvements: Trends and Best Practices in The Global Manufacturing Chain”, Seminar: “Responsibility Requirements and Social Standards According to the Electronic Industry Citizenship Coalition (EICC) - An “Entrance Ticket” for Enterprises in the industries of Mechanics, Hardware, Electricity and Electronics to Enter The Global Manufacturing Chain”. Both, exhibitors and visitors were contented with their participation, and signed many contracts and business cooperation agreements.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nFollowing above success, VIETNAM HARDWARE &amp; HAND TOOLS 2020 will be held from 18th June to 20th Dec, 2020 at Hanoi International Exhibition Center (ICE) 91 Tran Hung Dao Str., Hoan Kiem Dist., Hanoi, Vietnam.The exhibition is expected to attract 300 enterprises from 20 different countries and territories exhibiting on the area of 5.000m2 and welcome 15.000 visitors during four exhibition days. This year, the exhibition continues to have its honor of being supported by Vietnam Association of Mechanical Industry (VAMI) and Ho Chi Minh City’s Association of Mechanical – Electrical Enterprises (HAMEE) with consultancy for all activities before and during the exhibition.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'VIETNAM INTERNATIONAL HARDWARE & HANDTOOLS EXHIBITION – VIETNAM HARDWARE & HAND TOOLS 2020', 'The success of Vietnam Expo is not only a first-ever trade promotion event of Vietnam held annually for nearly three decades. It is also a well-known event because of the diversity of products, quality products - prestigious brand - creativity of Vietnam that introduces international friends.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '207-autosave-v1', '', '', '2019-07-04 10:32:18', '2019-07-04 03:32:18', '', 207, 'http://elevatorexpo.com.vn/207-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
